  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cocoa value chain development HELPING SMALL PRODUCERS TO DIVERSIFY CROPS IN NORTHERN NICARAGUA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Incomes increased by 25%; - 700 jobs created; - 400 small producers supported; - 140 ha of high yielding grafted cocoa established in agroforestry systems to produce by year 4 over 1,000 hundredweight of cocoa, generating $280,000 in sales for the Soppexcca business.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to develop the cocoa value chain and ultimately create a sustainable cocoa business in the medium term that will also generate significant economic, social &amp; environmental benefits for small coffee &amp; cocoa farmers and communities. There is a specific focus on developing capacity across the value chain from production, including managing a cocoa nursery using grafted cocoa, certification, quality control &amp; traceability processes, harvesting, post harvesting, product transformation (choc sales to nat. market) &amp; commercialisation (incl. business plan development), as well as support to develop org., admin. &amp; financial capacity, and dissemination of best practice nationally.</narrative>
  </description>
